name: bombay-hook-national-wildlife-refuge-quarterly-narrative-report-november-december-and-ja-1-c5418
notes: This narrative report for Bombay Hook NWR outlines Refuge accomplishments from November, 1941 through January, 1942. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, furbearers, predators, rodents, mammals, and raptors- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments. The public relations section of the report describes Refuge visitors and violations.
